parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Transmission Failure due to Insufficient Lubrication
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission due to insufficient lubrication can cause the transmission to overheat, leading to massive damage, failure, and potentially a fire, property damage, or a crash resulting in injuries or death.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Dual Fuel Tank Selector Valve Malfunction
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the dual fuel tank selector valve can cause an overfill condition in one of the fuel tanks, leading to fuel spillage and potentially causing a fire hazard.
symptoms: Fuel spillage from the main fuel tank
fuel spillage from the reserve fuel tank
fuel overflowing from the main tank into the reserve tank
and fuel overflowing from the reserve tank into the main tank.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Tire tread separation can cause loss of vehicle control, leading to accidents, injuries, and fatalities. The intense vibration caused by the separation can also lead to loss of control, especially at high speeds.
symptoms: Sudden and intense vibration while driving
tire tread separating from the tire

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Rust damage to steel belts can weaken the tire's structural integrity, leading to tire failure, loss of control, and accidents.
symptoms: Rust or corrosion on the steel belts
